{
  "text": "Similar reactions occur with carbonate and borate ions. As a result of this equilibrium, the pH of seawater is alkaline. The alkalinity of a seawater sample is expressed by the amount of hydrogen ion that is needed to convert all the weak acid anions to their unionized acids and it is given by expression (1), which regards the electroneutrality of the solution [CITATION_1] :",
